<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1/133: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-06T15:00:00-05:00">February
                                    6, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. A committee appointed by the Assembly of the League of Nations to
                            inaugurate a plan for the reorganization of the League’s technical work
                            will meet at The Hague beginning February 7. For your strictly
                            confidential information, the Department has not yet determined the
                            attitude it will adopt toward the new organization and would prefer not
                            to be approached on the subject at this time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>